  res.json({ status: 'ok' });
});
```

---

### 🟡 LOW — No Request Body Size Limit (Future Risk)

No `express.json()` or `express.urlencoded()` middleware is configured. If POST/PUT routes are added later without a size limit, the app will be vulnerable to payload-based DoS attacks.

**Recommendation:** Set this up proactively:

```js
// ✅ Limit body size before adding any POST/PUT routes
app.use(express.json({ limit: '10kb' }));
app.use(express.urlencoded({ extended: true, limit: '10kb' }));
```

